text.section:
Articles of extension shall include:
The date the existence of the corporation expired under the terms of its charter;
The date to which the existence of the corporation is to be extended, or a statement that the existence of the corporation is to be perpetual;
A statement that the reinstatement and extension have been approved in the manner and by the vote required by this article and the corporation's charter, and a statement of the manner of approval; and
A statement that the corporation has been in continuous operation since before the date of expiration.
